verbose_text: In the first example, many reports agree that K-Rta binds to short segments of the Mta promoter directly, yet other reports propose that K-Rta binds only indirectly to the Mta promoter (and others), by " piggybacking " onto DNA bound RBP-Jk.
evidence: K-Rta binds only indirectly to the Mta promoter (and others), by "piggybacking" onto DNA-bound RBP-Jk
